
Lets say we have 5 different classes (Below is the order for execution of Annotations in TestNg 

@BeforeSuite ---->1
@beforeTest ---->1
@BeforeClass ---->5
@BeforeGroups depends on the number of specific groups
@BeforeMethods ----> depends on number of @Test in one class
@Test ----> once for itself
@AfetrMethods
@AfterGroups
@AfetrClass
@AfterTest
@AfterSuite

Headles mode: Browser with GUI----> 60%

How do you run all testcases collectively?
.xml
for eg: Smoke has 40 cases---> smoke.xml
for eg: Regression has 20 cases-----? regression.xml

